WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:40.106 --> 00:41.940
Water my houseplants
and feed the dog.

00:41.941 --> 00:43.642
Make sure those utilities
get paid.

00:43.643 --> 00:46.144
Just relax, will you, Kelly?

00:46.145 --> 00:48.013
You're beginning to sound
like my mother.

00:48.014 --> 00:49.848
Just worry
about getting on the boat.

00:49.849 --> 00:52.018
Hey, what's this guy like,
anyway?

00:53.018 --> 00:55.220
I don't know. Sounded kind
of cute on the phone, though.

00:55.221 --> 00:57.188
Uh-huh.

00:57.189 --> 00:59.757
Well, any man that's gonna take
his two kids around the world

00:59.758 --> 01:00.959
can't be all that bad.

01:00.960 --> 01:02.627
He's in for a big surprise.

01:02.628 --> 01:04.763
I know. I'm not gonna stick
around to see what happens.

01:04.763 --> 01:05.764
I wish you were going with me.

01:05.765 --> 01:07.765
I do too.

01:08.034 --> 01:09.735
Think of the ports
you're gonna go to.

01:09.736 --> 01:11.736
I know.

01:14.206 --> 01:16.675
Thanks a lot.
See you in six weeks.

01:16.676 --> 01:17.942
Have a good time.
- Okay.

01:17.943 --> 01:22.380
Don't forget to write me!

01:22.381 --> 01:24.815
You've done most of the work
on the boat yourself

01:24.816 --> 01:26.118
in preparation for this trip.

01:26.119 --> 01:27.285
How long did all that take?

01:27.286 --> 01:29.388
It took us three years.
It's a...

01:29.389 --> 01:31.290
She's a converted
North Sea trawler.

01:31.291 --> 01:34.993
She's strong.
It's just a big family project.

01:34.994 --> 01:37.862
And there's been controversy
that you're placing the girls

01:37.863 --> 01:39.731
in a little bit of danger
with a voyage like this.

01:39.732 --> 01:42.100
Any thoughts on that?

01:42.101 --> 01:44.341
Well, I think we've taken
all the necessary precautions.

01:45.004 --> 01:47.071
Um, the girls have been raised
around boats.

01:47.072 --> 01:48.940
I think there's an element
of danger

01:48.941 --> 01:50.408
in just about anything you do
in life.

01:50.409 --> 01:51.976
Even living in the city.

01:51.977 --> 01:53.311
How do you feel
about this adventure?

01:53.312 --> 01:54.946
I think it's the best thing

01:54.947 --> 01:57.081
I've ever done in my whole life.

01:57.082 --> 01:58.717
What do you think
about all this?

01:58.718 --> 02:00.285
I think it's great.

02:00.286 --> 02:02.888
It sounds
like an extraordinary trip.

02:02.889 --> 02:04.655
I wish I could go with you,
but good luck.

02:04.656 --> 02:06.656
Thank you.

02:14.366 --> 02:16.366
All right?

02:18.905 --> 02:20.871
Oh, I'm so glad you came.

02:20.872 --> 02:22.874
Oh, okay. Bye-bye.

02:22.875 --> 02:24.275
Listen to your dad.

02:24.276 --> 02:25.842
I will.
- You have a great trip.

02:25.843 --> 02:26.877
Okay, we'll be fine.

02:26.878 --> 02:27.879
Take care of her.

02:27.880 --> 02:29.114
Bye-bye.

02:29.115 --> 02:30.716
Hey, gramps. Oh.

02:30.717 --> 02:32.282
Hey.
- You take care for now.

02:32.283 --> 02:33.351
We'll be okay.

02:33.352 --> 02:35.888
I know. I know you will.

02:42.261 --> 02:43.728
Um, I'm glad
you haven't left yet.

02:43.729 --> 02:44.895
Is Mr. Maclaine on board?

02:44.896 --> 02:47.264
Yeah. I'm Maclaine.

02:47.265 --> 02:49.601
<i>Well, hi. I'm Kelly Zimmerman
from World Magazine.</i>

02:49.602 --> 02:50.769
Hi.
- Nice to meet you.

02:50.770 --> 02:52.269
Where's Peterson?

02:52.270 --> 02:54.172
He broke his leg
in a skydiving assignment.

02:54.173 --> 02:55.740
So I'm taking his place.

02:55.741 --> 02:57.508
Oh, no, you're not.

02:57.509 --> 02:59.609
I didn't agree to take anybody
but Peterson.

02:59.610 --> 03:02.079
Would you rather have a guy
with a broken leg

03:02.080 --> 03:03.448
or the best reporter
on the magazine?

03:03.449 --> 03:05.716
I'd rather have a man
that can sail.

03:05.717 --> 03:07.385
And Peterson's a sailor.

03:07.386 --> 03:08.386
What makes you think I'm not?

03:08.387 --> 03:09.588
Are you?

03:09.589 --> 03:11.691
No, but I'm a quick learner.

03:12.691 --> 03:15.592
Courtney, cut the shore power.
I'll be right back.

03:15.593 --> 03:18.430
I'm not taking
any inexperienced woman.

03:18.431 --> 03:20.332
Which is it?
The inexperienced or the woman?

03:20.333 --> 03:21.600
Both.

03:21.601 --> 03:23.368
Why don't you try
telling my editor that?

03:23.369 --> 03:25.336
That's exactly
what I'm gonna do.

03:25.337 --> 03:27.037
While you're at it,
why don't you tell her

03:27.038 --> 03:28.906
to give me a raise, huh?

03:28.907 --> 03:31.883
You can tell her
it's combat pay!

03:36.883 --> 03:39.951
Hi. Is he always like this?

03:39.952 --> 03:42.931
Only when he hasn't eaten.

03:51.931 --> 03:53.731
We should be leaving
in about an hour.

03:53.732 --> 03:55.735
The winds will be good then.

03:56.735 --> 03:58.836
Here he comes.

03:58.837 --> 04:00.805
Huh, it doesn't look good.

04:00.806 --> 04:02.341
He'll be going.

04:02.342 --> 04:05.044
He can't afford to go without
the money from the magazine.

04:06.044 --> 04:08.113
Okay, there'll be
no smoking on board.

04:08.114 --> 04:10.114
Yes, sir.

04:11.849 --> 04:13.385
Let's get this bucket moving!

04:13.386 --> 04:15.887
Yeah!
- We're leaving, we're leaving!

04:15.888 --> 04:17.887
Going at last! Great!

04:18.024 --> 04:20.024
Get the three lines, Sam.

06:58.317 --> 06:59.751
<i>First day.</i>

06:59.752 --> 07:03.388
<i>Left the coast and sailed west
into the open sea.</i>

07:03.389 --> 07:04.989
<i>The wind is from the south.</i>

07:04.990 --> 07:07.993
<i>Everything's running smoothly.</i>

07:07.994 --> 07:09.626
<i>I'm glad Kelly is onboard.</i>

07:09.627 --> 07:13.330
<i>She's catching on quick
and will make a good sailor.</i>

07:13.331 --> 07:16.266
<i>I just hope
Dad gives her a chance.</i>

07:16.267 --> 07:18.302
<i>It's hard to believe after
all the years of planning</i>

07:18.303 --> 07:20.769
<i>we're finally on our way.</i>

07:51.769 --> 07:53.537
There you are.

07:53.538 --> 07:56.474
I was beginning to think
you'd fallen overboard.

07:56.475 --> 07:59.947
Now, let's see
if we can find Raggedy Ann.

08:02.947 --> 08:04.381
Shh.

08:04.382 --> 08:05.650
Don't tell on me.

08:05.651 --> 08:07.083
Please, don't tell on me.

08:07.084 --> 08:08.419
Please.

08:08.420 --> 08:09.987
What are you doing here?

08:09.988 --> 08:11.321
I'm an orphan.

08:11.322 --> 08:15.293
If they catch me, they're gonna
break my legs again.

08:16.293 --> 08:17.427
They broke your legs?

08:17.428 --> 08:18.496
Yeah.

08:18.497 --> 08:20.931
They tortured us and everything.

08:20.932 --> 08:22.932
You won't tell on me, will you?

08:23.601 --> 08:25.601
My dad's gonna find you anyways.

08:26.004 --> 08:27.003
No, he won't.

08:27.004 --> 08:29.207
Not if you can keep a secret.

08:29.208 --> 08:30.441
What are you gonna do?

08:30.442 --> 08:32.443
Stick with the boat
till it reaches China,

08:32.445 --> 08:35.678
then I'm gonna be a pirate
and get lots of money.

08:35.679 --> 08:38.587
Sam, lunch is ready.

08:43.587 --> 08:45.587
What are you doing down there?

08:46.291 --> 08:48.291
Please?

08:50.562 --> 08:53.130
Just looking for Penelope.

08:53.131 --> 08:55.503
Come on, let's go.

08:57.503 --> 09:00.271
I'm coming.

09:00.272 --> 09:02.272
Thanks.

09:02.374 --> 09:03.675
Can I get you anything?

09:03.676 --> 09:05.408
A book.

09:05.409 --> 09:10.148
Here, take Penelope.
She can keep you company.

09:10.149 --> 09:12.517
See you later.

09:12.518 --> 09:13.651
What's your name?

09:13.652 --> 09:15.085
Jesse.

09:15.086 --> 09:17.086
I'm Sam.

09:35.774 --> 09:37.980
Don't feed the dog at the table.

09:41.980 --> 09:43.981
Dad?
- Hmm?

09:43.982 --> 09:46.683
What do you call someone
who sneaks on a ship?

09:46.684 --> 09:48.385
A stowaway.

09:48.386 --> 09:50.754
There used to be lots of them
in the old days.

09:50.755 --> 09:52.656
What did they used to do
to them?

09:52.657 --> 09:54.697
They would either, um, put them
to work on the ship

09:55.059 --> 09:57.027
or they would,
uh, keelhaul them.

09:57.028 --> 09:59.163
What's that?

09:59.164 --> 10:01.931
So they would take them
and tie their hands and legs

10:01.932 --> 10:04.268
and drag them the length
of the keel underwater.

10:04.269 --> 10:06.638
The sharks got most of them.

10:06.639 --> 10:07.939
Gross.

10:07.940 --> 10:09.940
You wouldn't do a thing
like that, would you, Dad?

10:12.043 --> 10:14.436
It would depend upon
if it was a girl or not, Sam.

10:37.436 --> 10:40.006
Hey!

10:41.006 --> 10:45.943
Help!

10:51.984 --> 10:53.984
Oh, that always gives me
goose pimples.

10:54.019 --> 10:55.353
More coffee?
- No, thanks.

10:55.354 --> 10:57.220
It's your watch,
I'm gonna take a nap.

10:57.221 --> 10:59.156
Don't let the battery run
too long on the autopilot.

10:59.157 --> 11:00.758
We're gonna finish
our coffees first.

11:00.759 --> 11:02.759
Okay.

11:05.130 --> 11:07.064
He's lucky
Travis didn't see that.

11:07.065 --> 11:09.065
Especially,
since it's his plate.

11:35.094 --> 11:37.061
Jesse.

11:37.062 --> 11:39.376
Jesse, it's just me.

11:51.376 --> 11:53.866
Jesse?

12:14.866 --> 12:16.866
Jesse?

12:29.881 --> 12:31.248
What's up?

12:31.249 --> 12:33.868
Nothing.

12:49.868 --> 12:52.272
He fell over.

12:54.272 --> 12:55.505
Dad!

12:55.506 --> 12:57.508
Dad! Jesse fell over!

12:57.509 --> 12:59.109
What is it, Sam?

12:59.110 --> 13:01.378
You've gotta turn back.
He fell over!

13:01.379 --> 13:02.412
Who fell over?

13:02.413 --> 13:04.148
Hey, what's going on?

13:04.149 --> 13:06.149
There was a little boy, Dad.

13:06.150 --> 13:09.119
And he was hiding on the boat
and he's fallen overboard.

13:09.120 --> 13:10.989
What are you talking about, Sam?

13:10.990 --> 13:12.189
Know anything about this?
- No.

13:12.190 --> 13:14.090
This is his toothbrush
and paste.

13:14.091 --> 13:15.191
They were on the deck.

13:15.192 --> 13:16.460
Sam?

13:16.461 --> 13:19.964
I'm not lying, Dad.
Honest, I'm not lying.

13:19.965 --> 13:21.865
When was the last time
you saw him?

13:21.866 --> 13:24.072
Just before lunch.
He was hiding in the fo'c'sle.

13:27.072 --> 13:30.908
Okay, let's jibe.
Get the head sails.

14:03.908 --> 14:06.476
I see something about
two points off the port bow.

14:06.477 --> 14:08.477
Do you see it?

14:14.820 --> 14:16.820
There he is!

14:23.695 --> 14:25.296
Hey!

14:25.297 --> 14:28.936
Help!

14:30.936 --> 14:33.943
Hey!

14:38.943 --> 14:41.178
A little more to the port.

14:41.179 --> 14:43.179
Okay, hold that!

14:45.082 --> 14:47.183
Okay, coming to get you now.

14:47.184 --> 14:49.220
When you see it reaches,
reach up and get my hand.

14:49.221 --> 14:51.354
Now, reach it up. Come on.
There you go.

14:51.355 --> 14:53.291
Okay, got you.

14:53.292 --> 14:55.292
Okay.

14:56.061 --> 14:57.094
Come on. Come on.

14:57.095 --> 14:59.095
Let me give you a hand.

15:00.331 --> 15:02.331
Come on.

15:03.335 --> 15:04.868
Ah.

15:04.869 --> 15:06.875
Are you okay?

15:09.875 --> 15:12.249
Get him below deck.
- Come on, let's go. Let's go.

15:18.249 --> 15:20.249
Feeling better?

15:23.054 --> 15:25.856
Here we go. Best way
in the world to warm up.

15:25.857 --> 15:28.097
Does anybody else know
you're on this ship?

15:33.097 --> 15:36.301
Sam tells me you're an orphan.
Is that right?

15:36.302 --> 15:37.968
Yeah.

15:37.969 --> 15:39.903
Okay. I've gotta notify
the Coast Guard

15:39.904 --> 15:42.239
that you're aboard.

15:42.240 --> 15:44.916
Do you have any relatives
anywhere?

15:51.916 --> 15:53.916
No.

15:56.855 --> 15:58.998
Not even an aunt or an uncle?

16:05.998 --> 16:09.066
I have a mother.

16:09.067 --> 16:11.534
But she doesn't know I'm here.

16:11.535 --> 16:15.272
I have four brothers

16:15.273 --> 16:18.308
and sisters,
and they all think I'm dead.

16:18.309 --> 16:21.845
I don't know
what's gonna happen.

16:21.846 --> 16:23.781
It's okay. It's okay, Jesse.

16:23.782 --> 16:25.782
Everything's gonna be okay.

16:26.017 --> 16:28.451
Everything's gonna be all right.

16:59.451 --> 17:02.185
Does the world get to hear
about it?

17:02.186 --> 17:03.854
Hmm.

17:03.855 --> 17:05.989
I probably
wouldn't be interested.

17:05.990 --> 17:07.990
Give it a try.

17:09.894 --> 17:12.194
I was just thinking
how lucky that boy was

17:12.195 --> 17:13.631
we found him out here today.

17:13.632 --> 17:16.036
Ah, he sure was.

17:18.036 --> 17:19.036
Why do you do it?

17:19.037 --> 17:20.738
What, the voyage?

17:20.739 --> 17:23.342
Yeah. The risks, everything.

17:24.301 --> 17:25.742
I just couldn't think
of a better way

17:25.742 --> 17:27.176
to get close to my daughters

17:27.178 --> 17:29.313
and show them
who their father is.

17:29.314 --> 17:31.515
Yeah. The bad parts
as well as the good.

17:31.516 --> 17:34.488
Right.

17:36.488 --> 17:38.689
Well, I sure hope
it all works out for you.

17:38.690 --> 17:40.690
It already has.

17:41.026 --> 17:43.026
Most of it, anyway.

17:44.797 --> 17:46.197
Coast Guard
is gonna pick the boy up

17:46.198 --> 17:47.497
when we reach the Aleutians.

17:47.498 --> 17:50.101
They've had an all-points
out on him for days.

17:50.102 --> 17:52.635
That kid's got a lot of spirit.

17:52.636 --> 17:55.048
My kind of kid.

