<i>♪ What shall we do
With a drunken sailor? ♪</i>

18:12.990 --> 18:15.960
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

18:15.961 --> 18:24.235
<i>♪ Way, hey, up she rises ♪</i>

18:24.236 --> 18:26.303
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

18:26.304 --> 18:33.410
<i>♪ Put him in the bilge
And make him drink it ♪</i>

18:33.411 --> 18:35.880
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

18:35.881 --> 18:42.852
<i>♪ Way, hey, up she rises ♪</i>

18:43.020 --> 18:45.221
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

18:45.222 --> 18:51.895
<i>♪ Shave him in the belly
With a rusty razor ♪</i>

18:51.896 --> 18:53.931
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

18:53.932 --> 19:01.204
<i>♪ Way, hey, up she rises ♪</i>

19:01.205 --> 19:03.339
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

19:03.340 --> 19:09.958
<i>♪ Put him in the bunk
With the captain's daughter ♪</i>

19:10.015 --> 19:11.781
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

19:11.782 --> 19:18.788
<i>♪ Way, hey, up she rises ♪</i>

19:18.789 --> 19:20.657
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

19:20.658 --> 19:27.197
<i>♪ That's what you do
With a drunken sailor ♪</i>

19:27.198 --> 19:28.966
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

19:28.967 --> 19:36.874
<i>♪ Way, hey, up she rises ♪</i>

19:36.875 --> 19:43.279
<i>♪ Earlye in the morning ♪</i>

19:43.280 --> 19:45.047
<i>Seventeenth day.</i>

19:45.048 --> 19:48.286
<i>Found a sick pelican on deck
and named him Pinocchio.</i>

19:48.287 --> 19:51.322
<i>He's amazingly tame
since we fed him.</i>

19:51.323 --> 19:54.892
<i>We should reach the Aleutians
and Dutch Harbor tomorrow.</i>

19:54.893 --> 19:57.595
<i>We'll really miss Jesse.</i>

19:57.596 --> 19:59.296
<i>It's been exactly one year today</i>

19:59.297 --> 20:01.297
<i>since Mom died.</i>

20:02.366 --> 20:04.334
How's he doing?
- He's settling right in.

20:04.335 --> 20:06.335
Watch it.

20:07.137 --> 20:09.209
Okay, Jaws, open up.

20:11.209 --> 20:12.976
He eats like you, Sam.

20:12.977 --> 20:14.977
Hey.

20:18.182 --> 20:20.550
Look at him eat. Gosh.

20:20.551 --> 20:22.252
It's too big for him.

20:22.253 --> 20:24.788
He can eat anything.
- Come on, baby.

20:30.561 --> 20:32.162
How's it going?

20:32.163 --> 20:34.730
Calm as a horse trough.

20:34.731 --> 20:36.267
Okay, I'm gonna go below,

20:36.268 --> 20:38.302
double-check the weather
and get some shut-eye.

20:38.303 --> 20:39.670
Call me if you need anything.

20:39.671 --> 20:41.671
Okay. Sweet dreams.

20:45.176 --> 20:46.876
You're turning
into a pretty good sailor.

20:46.877 --> 20:48.877
There's nothing else to do.

21:32.289 --> 21:35.225
Dad. You'd better come on deck.
The wind is really picking up.

21:35.226 --> 21:37.226
Okay, I'm coming.

21:39.363 --> 21:41.363
Let's go.

21:47.070 --> 21:49.910
Head her up into the wind!

21:51.910 --> 21:53.375
What?

21:53.376 --> 21:55.812
Head her up into the wind!

21:55.813 --> 21:57.280
Courtney, go below!

21:57.281 --> 22:01.085
Get my harnesses
and foul weather gear.

22:01.086 --> 22:03.720
You should have called me
sooner.

22:03.721 --> 22:05.422
Okay,
keep her headed into the wind.

22:05.423 --> 22:06.923
I've gotta drop the sail!

22:06.924 --> 22:08.961
Okay!

22:34.452 --> 22:36.820
What's happening?
- We're getting into a storm.

22:36.821 --> 22:38.821
You'd better stay down here.

22:53.003 --> 22:56.307
Here. Watch the boom.

22:57.307 --> 23:00.075
Go down below and make sure
everything's secure.

23:00.076 --> 23:02.144
Check the bilges
and then come back

23:02.145 --> 23:04.554
and help me with the main, okay?

23:10.554 --> 23:12.554
I got it. Go below
and get yourself warm.

23:13.057 --> 23:14.490
You did a good job!

23:14.491 --> 23:16.393
How about some coffee?

23:16.394 --> 23:18.442
Later.

23:32.442 --> 23:33.509
How's Sam?

23:33.510 --> 23:35.510
She's still asleep.

23:36.047 --> 23:38.248
That kid doesn't have a nerve
in her body.

23:38.249 --> 23:40.519
There you go.
- Thanks.

23:42.519 --> 23:44.519
Oh, thanks.

23:46.356 --> 23:48.592
I hope this doesn't last long.

23:48.593 --> 23:51.430
It could last for days.

23:52.430 --> 23:56.066
Oh, God. Not again.

23:56.067 --> 23:59.378
Take it. Ugh, take it.

24:08.378 --> 24:10.378
Are you all right?

24:59.297 --> 25:02.766
This is a 2200 hour check-in.
Do you copy, over?

25:02.767 --> 25:04.201
Everybody into their life vests.

25:04.202 --> 25:05.402
Courtney, take the helm.
Kelly, get the life raft ready.

25:05.403 --> 25:07.002
What is it?

25:07.003 --> 25:08.770
Get your shoes on.

25:08.771 --> 25:09.940
Jesse, get over here.

25:09.941 --> 25:11.941
Get over here.

25:43.807 --> 25:45.807
Put it out here!

25:48.045 --> 25:50.045
Oh, God.

25:50.949 --> 25:54.116
Let's put it over the side!

25:54.117 --> 25:56.555
Hang on to that rope!

25:57.555 --> 25:59.848
Come on!

26:24.848 --> 26:27.517
Dad! Dad, we're sinking!

26:27.518 --> 26:29.085
Sam!
Come on, come on.

26:29.086 --> 26:30.487
Everybody in the life boat!

26:30.488 --> 26:32.422
Jesse, get in the life raft!

26:32.423 --> 26:34.423
Take hold of Sam's hand!

26:37.161 --> 26:39.529
Mayday, mayday, mayday.
This is a mayday.

26:39.530 --> 26:41.498
<i>Mayday, mayday.
The yacht Cloudy.</i>

26:41.499 --> 26:43.499
We are sinking, we are sinking.

26:48.205 --> 26:50.172
Longitude 26 degrees.
10 minutes north. Mayday!

26:50.173 --> 26:51.174
Dad!

26:51.175 --> 26:53.175
Mayday, mayday!

26:55.946 --> 26:57.581
Get in the raft! Kelly, hurry!

26:57.582 --> 26:58.781
Move forward!

26:58.782 --> 26:59.816
Come on, move! Go!

26:59.817 --> 27:01.084
We're sinking!

27:01.085 --> 27:03.085
It's okay, sweetheart.

27:07.057 --> 27:09.230
Okay, push off. Push off.

27:13.230 --> 27:15.913
Keep your weight in the center!

28:02.913 --> 28:05.983
Okay, everybody hold on now.

28:06.904 --> 28:08.384
All right,
here comes another one now.

28:08.385 --> 28:10.385
Hold on tight!

28:13.324 --> 28:14.324
Dad!

28:14.325 --> 28:16.325
Sam!

28:17.228 --> 28:18.761
I've got Sam!

28:18.762 --> 28:20.063
Get the boy! Get the boy!

28:20.064 --> 28:21.897
Courtney!

28:21.898 --> 28:23.898
I got him.

28:24.167 --> 28:26.870
Help me!

28:26.871 --> 28:29.972
Come on, let's get on the
beach. The beach is right here.

28:29.973 --> 28:31.973
I got her. I got her.

28:39.115 --> 28:40.784
Are you okay?

28:40.785 --> 28:41.852
Yeah.

28:41.853 --> 28:43.452
Where are the others?

28:43.453 --> 28:45.922
I don't know.

28:45.923 --> 28:49.861
Kelly!

28:50.861 --> 28:52.861
There they are! Hold her!

28:56.567 --> 28:59.335
Hold on to him!

28:59.336 --> 29:01.336
Okay. I got him.

29:05.076 --> 29:08.748
You're all right.
You're all right, come on.

29:10.748 --> 29:12.848
Come on.

29:12.849 --> 29:14.351
I can't get up!

29:14.352 --> 29:16.352
Yes, you can. Come on!
- Come on.

29:17.020 --> 29:18.854
I'm freezing!

29:18.855 --> 29:21.290
Okay. We'll get a fire going.

29:21.291 --> 29:23.026
Where's Mushroom?

29:23.027 --> 29:25.461
Don't worry about him.
- He can swim.

29:25.462 --> 29:27.931
Whatever happened to Pinocchio?

29:27.932 --> 29:29.199
He just flew away.

29:29.200 --> 29:31.066
No!

29:31.067 --> 29:32.870
Get them to lean to the rocks
up here.

29:32.871 --> 29:34.270
Where are we?

29:34.271 --> 29:36.271
Somewhere on the coast
of Alaska.

30:27.191 --> 30:28.258
What is it?

30:28.259 --> 30:29.425
Sea lions.

30:29.426 --> 30:31.426
Lions?

30:34.131 --> 30:35.798
Are they dangerous?

30:35.799 --> 30:37.799
I don't think so.

30:39.135 --> 30:40.937
We'll just give them
a lot of room.

30:40.938 --> 30:42.938
Hey, Mushroom. Come back!

30:44.241 --> 30:47.814
Mushroom, get back here.
- Come on.

30:50.814 --> 30:52.943
Come here.

31:53.943 --> 31:55.943
You see anything?

31:56.247 --> 31:58.247
Nothing.

31:59.016 --> 32:01.483
Not even a house or anything.

32:01.484 --> 32:04.487
We'll find something.

32:04.488 --> 32:07.359
I'll bet we're the first people
who ever set foot here.

32:10.341 --> 32:12.261
Hey, Samantha, what about
that candy bar you had?

32:12.262 --> 32:13.930
I ate it.

32:13.931 --> 32:15.097
Hey, what's that?

32:15.098 --> 32:16.966
Silly Putty.

32:16.967 --> 32:20.269
Hey, that thing work?
- No.

32:20.270 --> 32:21.837
All right, is that everything?

32:21.838 --> 32:23.838
Not even a knife or fork
to eat with.

32:24.007 --> 32:26.275
There's nothing to eat anyway.

32:26.276 --> 32:29.312
Hey, wait a minute,
where did you get that?

32:29.313 --> 32:31.581
I just traded some comic books.

32:31.582 --> 32:33.582
I'm glad you did.

32:34.352 --> 32:36.185
Okay, I want you
to get a fire going.

32:36.186 --> 32:38.121
I'm gonna see
if I can get us some food.

32:38.122 --> 32:40.855
Can I go?
- Okay.

32:40.856 --> 32:41.857
Me too?

32:41.858 --> 32:43.293
No, you stay here.
- Please?

32:43.294 --> 32:46.630
Stick with the women, kid,
you'll have more fun.

32:46.631 --> 32:49.097
Hey, it's working.

32:49.098 --> 32:51.100
<i>Ever dream of
getting away from it all?</i>

32:51.101 --> 32:52.969
<i>Of going to a land
where the air is pure?</i>

32:52.970 --> 32:55.238
I wouldn't mind
a little smog right now.

32:55.239 --> 32:57.774
Save those batteries
for the weather and the news.

32:57.775 --> 33:00.075
Okay, Dad.

33:00.076 --> 33:01.177
Yeah.

33:01.178 --> 33:03.255
All right. Let's go.

33:11.255 --> 33:12.689
You ever do any hunting before?

33:12.690 --> 33:14.190
No.

33:14.191 --> 33:17.326
Okay. We just gotta
stay close together

33:17.327 --> 33:19.162
and be quiet, all right?

33:19.163 --> 33:21.278
Okay.

34:07.278 --> 34:09.078
What are they?

34:09.079 --> 34:10.346
Caribou.

34:10.347 --> 34:11.480
Okay, stay close to me.

34:11.481 --> 34:13.889
Mushroom, stay.

35:46.943 --> 35:50.655
Hey, Travis, over here!

35:58.655 --> 36:00.655
There's one over there.

36:14.271 --> 36:15.471
Okay.

36:15.472 --> 36:17.339
Better wait back there.

36:17.340 --> 36:19.340
Go on.

36:51.240 --> 36:54.177
Come here, Jesse.
Give me a hand.

37:04.021 --> 37:07.027
Okay, just get behind her
and push.

37:11.027 --> 37:14.431
Come on. Get down there.

37:17.233 --> 37:18.935
Come on, Jesse. Push.

37:18.936 --> 37:21.875
Watch out for those horns.

37:57.875 --> 37:58.841
What are they?

37:58.842 --> 38:01.276
Musk ox.

38:01.277 --> 38:03.918
I've only seen them in pictures.

38:07.918 --> 38:10.419
Mean-looking dudes.

38:10.420 --> 38:12.254
Looks like prime rib to me.

38:12.255 --> 38:14.936
Let's go.

38:25.936 --> 38:27.936
Hold the dog.

39:17.686 --> 39:19.686
Mushroom!

40:23.853 --> 40:26.291
Maybe we should try
something smaller.

40:27.291 --> 40:29.865
Yeah.

40:35.865 --> 40:39.968
The hunters are coming!
The hunters are coming!

40:39.969 --> 40:41.337
Did you get anything?

40:41.338 --> 40:43.272
No, just some eggs, sweetheart.
Come here.

40:43.273 --> 40:46.442
Good.
Courtney can make an omelet.

40:46.443 --> 40:48.176
They got some eggs!

40:48.177 --> 40:50.212
Good. How many?

40:50.213 --> 40:52.284
Let's see.

40:54.284 --> 40:55.683
That's it?

40:55.684 --> 40:57.684
Didn't find anything?

40:59.222 --> 41:01.122
We'll get something tomorrow.

41:01.123 --> 41:03.262
But I'm hungry today.

41:05.262 --> 41:07.263
Hey. What's this?

41:07.264 --> 41:09.198
We found it at the beach.

41:09.199 --> 41:12.201
Isn't she cute?
- She's seems friendly enough.

41:12.202 --> 41:15.370
She must have been hurt
in the storm or something.

41:15.371 --> 41:17.973
Shh. Here's the news.

41:17.974 --> 41:20.209
<i>Coast Guard is searching
for a small sailing vessel</i>

41:20.210 --> 41:22.076
<i>missing since Wednesday night</i>

41:22.077 --> 41:24.946
<i>when a storm swept across
the northern Pacific.</i>

41:24.947 --> 41:26.948
<i>The vessel,
owned by a Seattle family...</i>

41:26.949 --> 41:30.118
That's us.
We're gonna be famous.

41:30.119 --> 41:32.555
<i>The search is being conducted
in that area.</i>

41:32.556 --> 41:34.455
<i>In Juneau today,</i>

41:34.456 --> 41:37.993
<i>the governor stated that
energy consumption in the...</i>

41:37.994 --> 41:40.562
Well, at least,
they know we're missing.

41:40.563 --> 41:43.366
They're looking
in the wrong area.

41:43.367 --> 41:46.301
Well, If they don't find us
there, they'll come here.

41:46.302 --> 41:47.303
Right, Dad?

41:47.304 --> 41:49.304
Right.

41:53.976 --> 41:55.977
I just can't stop thinking
about food.

41:55.978 --> 41:58.147
Think of something else.

41:58.148 --> 42:00.917
That's what my mom
always used to tell us.

42:00.918 --> 42:02.317
Like what?

42:02.318 --> 42:05.855
Like boiled rattlesnake bile
mixed with the blood of a toad.

42:05.856 --> 42:07.321
What's bile?

42:07.322 --> 42:09.959
That green stuff
that comes out of their mouths

42:09.960 --> 42:11.828
when you run them over.

42:11.829 --> 42:13.829
Yuck.

42:15.465 --> 42:16.966
Hey, are you okay?

42:16.967 --> 42:19.201
I'm fine.

42:19.202 --> 42:21.437
Think we have any chance
of walking out of here?

42:21.438 --> 42:24.138
Not with the kids.

42:24.139 --> 42:25.540
The best thing to do
you're looking for

42:25.541 --> 42:27.547
is just sit tight
and be prepared.

42:30.547 --> 42:32.547
They'll extend the search area.

43:02.478 --> 43:04.478
Sorry things haven't
worked out better for you.

43:06.215 --> 43:08.286
It hasn't been too bad so far.

43:10.286 --> 43:13.025
Well, I think we're lucky
Peterson broke his leg.

43:15.025 --> 43:16.325
He didn't.

43:16.326 --> 43:18.995
I talked the editor into
letting me come in his place.

43:18.996 --> 43:20.996
You're kidding.

43:22.398 --> 43:24.398
It never pays to be sneaky.

43:26.168 --> 43:28.470
Well, at least
you'll have a good article

43:28.471 --> 43:30.571
for your magazine now.

43:30.572 --> 43:33.542
Yeah, it's already a book.

43:33.543 --> 43:38.548
<i>How Not to Sail Around the
World with Travis Maclaine.</i>

43:39.548 --> 43:42.021
I just hope
it has a happy ending.

43:45.021 --> 43:47.021
It will.

44:08.911 --> 44:10.178
I've got it.

44:10.179 --> 44:12.856
Get out of the water.

44:19.856 --> 44:21.424
Are you okay, honey?

44:21.425 --> 44:24.998
Cover her with this. Here.

44:27.998 --> 44:28.997
Kelly?

44:28.998 --> 44:30.466
Yeah.
- Give me a hand.

44:30.467 --> 44:32.535
Okay, hold on.

44:32.536 --> 44:34.536
Here you go.

44:49.085 --> 44:51.386
How is she doing?
- Not so good.

44:51.387 --> 44:54.890
Okay, just keep her warm.
I'm gonna get some food.

44:54.891 --> 44:56.125
Can I go?

44:56.126 --> 44:57.426
No, you stay here.

44:57.427 --> 45:00.530
When it stops raining,
you go after those berries.

45:03.298 --> 45:05.366
How are you feeling?

45:05.367 --> 45:07.370
I'm just cold.

45:07.371 --> 45:09.372
Okay, I'll be right back,
all right?

45:09.373 --> 45:11.373
Get you some food.

47:38.288 --> 47:42.857
I wish I could be you for a day
and you could be me.

47:42.858 --> 47:45.166
That way, I could catch a fish.

47:50.166 --> 47:53.782
You should do something
about your breath.

48:38.782 --> 48:40.952
Hey, look at that!

48:41.952 --> 48:43.952
Oh, my...
They're going to land.

48:54.130 --> 48:55.497
I wish we had a gun.

48:55.498 --> 48:57.832
Yeah.

48:57.833 --> 48:59.901
Hey,
I know how we can catch one.

48:59.902 --> 49:00.968
How?

49:00.969 --> 49:02.904
I saw it in a movie once.

49:02.905 --> 49:04.905
Come on.

49:31.132 --> 49:33.368
Yah! Get out of here!
Go on! Git!

49:33.369 --> 49:35.803
Hey! Hey! Hey! Git!

49:35.804 --> 49:40.375
Yah! Yah! Ah! Ah!

49:40.376 --> 49:42.109
Yah! Yah!

49:42.110 --> 49:44.449
Get out! Get out!
Get out of here!

49:47.449 --> 49:50.556
Get out! Get out!

49:53.556 --> 49:55.556
Yah!

49:56.458 --> 50:00.095
Get out of here! Yah!

50:00.096 --> 50:04.933
Yah! Yah!

50:04.934 --> 50:08.347
Yah! Get out of here!

51:09.398 --> 51:12.399
Okay.

51:12.400 --> 51:14.035
I got it!

51:14.036 --> 51:16.872
Don't let go.
- Oh, I won't. Oh, dear.

51:16.873 --> 51:18.205
I didn't believe
you could do it.

51:18.206 --> 51:20.396
All right, here, give me a hand.

51:41.396 --> 51:43.601
Dad!

51:45.601 --> 51:49.206
We were worried about you.

51:50.206 --> 51:51.540
Hey, you're looking good.

51:51.541 --> 51:54.174
I feel much better now.

51:54.175 --> 51:56.178
Kelly caught a goose.

51:56.179 --> 51:58.079
A goose?

51:58.179 --> 52:00.381
How did you get it?

52:00.382 --> 52:03.151
He was just flying around,
so I hit it with a rock.

52:03.152 --> 52:05.152
A rock?

52:05.154 --> 52:06.553
She caught it in the lake.

52:06.554 --> 52:07.355
Hey, no fair.

52:07.356 --> 52:08.989
Hey.

52:08.990 --> 52:09.991
Us men gotta stick together.

52:09.992 --> 52:11.959
Come here, you.

52:11.960 --> 52:15.964
I'm so glad everything's
gonna be okay from now on.

52:15.965 --> 52:17.499
So am I, sweetheart.

52:17.500 --> 52:19.267
Hey, Jesse,
you and I can retire.

52:19.268 --> 52:20.935
The women are doing the hunting.

52:20.936 --> 52:23.171
Yeah, and you can do the dishes
tomorrow too.

52:23.172 --> 52:25.172
I wish we had dishes.

52:26.476 --> 52:28.476
Pretty sunset.

52:57.139 --> 52:59.975
<i>No ships or planes in 45 days.</i>

52:59.976 --> 53:02.410
<i>Everyone's beginning
to lose hope.</i>

53:02.411 --> 53:04.946
<i>Dad goes hunting for food
every day,</i>

53:04.947 --> 53:08.183
<i>but the animals are hard
to catch without a gun.</i>

53:08.184 --> 53:09.817
<i>If we ever get out of here,</i>

53:09.818 --> 53:14.223
<i>I'll never eat another
blueberry as long as I live.</i>

53:14.224 --> 53:17.258
<i>Jesse and Kelly are like
part of the family now.</i>

53:17.259 --> 53:19.060
<i>It's hard to imagine</i>

53:19.061 --> 53:22.430
<i>most of our friends and family
back home think we're dead.</i>

53:22.431 --> 53:24.899
<i>It's already very cold.</i>

53:24.900 --> 53:26.900
<i>Last night,
it snowed for the first time</i>

53:27.036 --> 53:30.339
<i>but didn't settle.</i>

53:30.340 --> 53:33.844
<i>Dad's trying to find a way out
over the mountains.</i>

53:34.844 --> 53:36.844
<i>I hope he makes it.</i>

54:30.099 --> 54:32.099
Hey, look at this one.

54:33.001 --> 54:34.602
Let's see.

54:34.603 --> 54:37.138
Yeah, that's good.

54:37.139 --> 54:39.008
Oh, look what I found.
- Ow!

54:39.009 --> 54:40.808
Oh, neato.

54:40.809 --> 54:43.345
That was mine!

54:43.346 --> 54:45.980
All right, don't get so crabby.

54:45.981 --> 54:48.850
Crabby?

54:48.851 --> 54:50.851
Can you get it?

54:53.021 --> 54:56.960
Hey! Anybody hungry?

54:57.960 --> 54:59.828
Come and get it!

54:59.829 --> 55:01.796
All you can eat!

55:01.797 --> 55:03.797
Come on!

56:18.239 --> 56:19.441
What are they doing?

56:19.442 --> 56:21.109
They're fishing.

56:21.110 --> 56:24.913
Catching the salmon that
are going up river to spawn.

56:24.914 --> 56:28.116
Mm. I love salmon.

56:28.117 --> 56:30.352
Well, if the bears
can catch them, so can we.

56:30.353 --> 56:32.886
There's a good place
downriver here.

56:32.887 --> 56:34.989
What about the bears?

56:34.990 --> 56:37.916
We'll give them lots of room
and keep our eyes open.

57:27.943 --> 57:29.943
Oh. On your left.

57:31.880 --> 57:33.880
Daddy!

58:23.030 --> 58:27.271
I got it.
I got it! I got it.

58:44.286 --> 58:46.461
Mushroom!

58:53.461 --> 58:54.462
There it go...

58:54.463 --> 58:56.463
Yeah! Yeah!

59:17.420 --> 59:20.023
Hey, Mushy. Hey, go on.
- Go on, Mushy.

59:21.023 --> 59:23.124
Oh, that's great, kids.
- Good job.

59:23.125 --> 59:25.364
Come on, Jesse,
let's go get some more.

59:29.364 --> 59:30.966
Enough to last us
the whole year.

59:30.967 --> 59:32.967
Hope we don't need them.

59:34.402 --> 59:36.402
I think we ought to have
a celebration!

59:48.951 --> 59:51.919
<i>♪ I don't wanna die
For king or country ♪</i>

59:51.920 --> 59:53.922
<i>♪ I've got what I want ♪</i>

01:00:03.632 --> 01:00:06.634
<i>♪ All I wanna be ♪</i>

01:00:06.635 --> 01:00:13.358
<i>♪ All I need to be is me ♪</i>

01:00:54.250 --> 01:00:56.651
Hey, If, uh, I go dance
with Kelly,

01:00:56.652 --> 01:00:57.685
would you dance with Jesse?

01:00:57.686 --> 01:00:59.686
Okay.

01:00:59.922 --> 01:01:02.756
Uh, excuse me, young man, may I?

01:01:02.757 --> 01:01:04.859
Yeah, you may.

01:01:04.860 --> 01:01:06.860
Thank you.

01:01:08.030 --> 01:01:13.369
<i>♪ Of all the loves
I've left behind me ♪</i>

01:01:15.369 --> 01:01:21.343
<i>♪ Looks on your face
Yes, they tell me ♪</i>

01:01:21.344 --> 01:01:27.485
<i>♪ That I should have never
Started loving you ♪</i>

01:01:30.485 --> 01:01:35.027
<i>♪ It was true when they said
That I was mean and cruel ♪</i>

01:01:38.027 --> 01:01:43.230
<i>♪ All the loves I've had
I've made them out as fools ♪</i>

01:01:43.231 --> 01:01:45.399
I don't like this slow stuff.

01:01:45.400 --> 01:01:51.372
<i>♪ Now the tide has turned
And I'm lonely too ♪</i>

01:01:51.373 --> 01:01:57.310
<i>♪ I should have never
Started loving you ♪</i>

01:01:57.311 --> 01:01:59.546
Do you want me
to turn the lights down?

01:01:59.547 --> 01:02:05.789
<i>♪ I should have never
Started loving you ♪</i>

01:02:07.789 --> 01:02:09.789
<i>♪ After all the things... ♪</i>

01:02:12.561 --> 01:02:14.229
It's a plane.

01:02:14.230 --> 01:02:15.363
They found us!

01:02:15.364 --> 01:02:16.931
Where is it?

01:02:16.932 --> 01:02:18.533
It's coming right on us!

01:02:18.534 --> 01:02:20.534
Get the flare gun!

01:02:21.036 --> 01:02:23.036
Come on. Let's go.

01:02:23.804 --> 01:02:25.006
Dad!

01:02:25.007 --> 01:02:28.910
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

01:02:28.911 --> 01:02:31.512
Hey! Over here!

01:02:37.885 --> 01:02:40.521
Hey! Hey!

01:02:46.661 --> 01:02:49.164
Hey!

01:03:01.909 --> 01:03:05.613
Here! Over here!
- Help!

01:03:05.614 --> 01:03:07.614
Help.

01:03:52.193 --> 01:03:54.261
You think they'll come back?

01:03:54.262 --> 01:03:56.262
Well, they're looking
in the right area.

01:03:58.233 --> 01:03:59.600
You know,
it's pretty chilly out.

01:03:59.601 --> 01:04:01.002
You sure you wanna sleep
out here?

01:04:01.003 --> 01:04:02.504
You bet.

01:04:02.505 --> 01:04:04.775
We don't wanna miss them again.

01:04:06.775 --> 01:04:09.209
How are you doing?

01:04:09.210 --> 01:04:11.011
I love you, Dad.

01:04:11.012 --> 01:04:13.083
I love you too, sweetheart.

01:04:15.083 --> 01:04:17.324
Good night.
- Good night.

01:04:23.324 --> 01:04:26.194
You know, I saw something
reflecting light today.

01:04:26.195 --> 01:04:28.062
It had to be either metal
or glass.

01:04:28.063 --> 01:04:29.196
Where?

01:04:29.197 --> 01:04:31.332
Just north of here.

01:04:31.333 --> 01:04:33.466
About a day's hike.
I'll check it out tomorrow.

01:04:33.467 --> 01:04:35.169
Eskimos, maybe.

01:04:35.170 --> 01:04:37.170
